  "created_at": "2016-06-02T08:09:27Z",
  "updated_at": "2016-10-24T08:12:12Z",
  "closed_at": "2016-10-24T08:12:12Z",
  "body": "May the component &lt;web&gt;, implemented as a webview or a iframe, have the ability to call APIs ?According to the messages sending by the content window ?\n\nThese messages' formats may abide by the communications's protocols between native renderer and the js-framework.\n\nTake calling  `event.openURL` as a example:\n\n```\ncontentWindow.postMessage({\n  type: 'weex',\n  content: [{\n    module: 'event',\n    method: 'openURL',\n    args: ['http://www.a.url'],\n  }],\n  from: 'http://www.content.window'\n}\n```\n\nThe web component's content may call some specified native APIs through this message tunnel.\n\nIn the above example's situation, the content page got the ability to call a page redirecting process to navigate the parent main page to another page, instead of making a page redirecting in the webview/iframe itself.\n",
